Date: Sat, 23 Jan 1999 12:25:59 -0500 (EST)
From: Ek' Tun <ektunbz@btl.net>

Discussion in Cayo and at particular meetings indicate a big concern for
the health of the reef as well. When there are 1000+ passengers per ship
flushing all their sewage into the sea over the course of a week, and
multiply that by several dozen ships each month, it would really have a
serious impact in the area. Does anyone know how the trash and sewage
disposal is handled? I've seen the beaches along the coast of Mexico,
and it's obvious that there is a major problem with trash washing
up...is it from the ships?
--
Ek' Tun
<ektunbz@btl.net>
