[2
Date: Sat, 23 Jan 1999 12:25:59 -0500 (EST)
From: Ray Auxillou <d023009c@dc.seflin.org>

There are some quite famous video tapes been shown on television in
Miami, of the kitchen staff of cruise ships dumping garbage, waste,
plastics, oils and all kinds of stuff off the ship at night. They have
to do every day, even with compactors on board. They don't take their
waste back to port, they dump at sea. Some big cruise ships paid
multi-million dollar fines. But it takes a passenger on board with a
video camera, or night time surveillance from airplanes to catch them
dumping.
Ray Auxillou
<d023009c@dc.seflin.org>
